Project Cruise — FAQ copy


What is Project Cruise?
A neutral ship that sails between the realms. It's built for two things at once: seeing the wider world, and giving different peoples a calm, common ground to meet and talk. Think of it as part voyage, part accord.

Who is allowed to travel?
Any verified guest from a recognised realm. Every traveller is confirmed with a Council-issued Veil Lens at booking and again at the gangway, so every realm sails knowing exactly who's aboard.

How does verification work?
The Inter-Realm Commerce Council provides the tools to confirm a guest's true nature. You'll complete verification when you book and present it again when you board. It protects everyone and keeps the ship neutral ground.

Whose laws apply on board?
It depends where we're sailing. Beyond any realm's waters, the ship runs under its own charter — the Accord — and its neutral rules hold. Within a realm's waters, that realm's laws apply. Every guest is told which is in force.

Will the ship accommodate my species?
Yes — tell us your realm and nature when you book and we ready the right cabin and table. A few examples: nightkin and vampires get sunless interior cabins with night dining; merfolk get saltwater berths; dryads get skylit garden cabins with a nectar table; emberkin get heat-rated obsidian staterooms. If your needs are unusual, ask and we'll arrange it.

What's included in the fare?
One all-inclusive price in crowns (◈) covers your cabin, meals suited to your nature, all port calls, and verification. No hidden charges once you're aboard.

Where do you sail?
Across the realms — the forests of Sylvangarde, the volcanic coast of Emberreach, the endless night of Nocturne, the sky isles of Skyhold, the frozen reaches of Frosthelm, and the twilight port of Duskmere. See our voyages for full itineraries.

How do I book?
Choose a voyage, complete verification, select your cabin and any accommodations for your species, and review your fare. You can also send word to the harbour chancery through our contact page and an envoy will help you plan.

Can rival realms really travel together safely?
That's the whole point. The ship is neutral ground, held on purpose — no thrones, no borders, no standing quarrels aboard. Guests come to rest and to talk, and the Accord keeps things even for everyone.

Can I change or cancel my crossing?
Yes — dates can be changed up to 30 days before departure. Reach the chancery and we'll help you rebook.
